description: This is mutation is rarely an independent stop, but usually a Mixture rank. It sounds the 12th harmonic, at 2/3' for the 8' harmonic series, or 1-1/3' for the 16' harmonic series. It is a fifth-sounding rank.
examplesDescription: Osiris contains a dozen examples of Vigesima Sesta, five at 2/3', two at 1-1/3', and the rest of unknown pitch. No examples of Vigessima-sexta are known.
